subject_prompt_600:
Nissan Cedric

The Cedric is a small four door hatchback developed by Nissan in collaboration with Renault. It is priced at around $30,000 and was introduced in 2008. The interior style of the car is a modified version of the Nissan Micra.

Nissan's CEO Carlos Ghosn had said on his twitter account that he was considering the idea of making a car with two doors in future and the potential benefits are big. A more open cabin could help to reduce stress due to limited space for occupants, a lot more legroom and possibly better visibility when driving at night.

On the other hand if you are used to the cramped dimensions of a four door car there is a good chance you would feel less at ease if you had to get out for a quick trip. The two door model of the car might make it more accessible to people who want the same comfort level but who have less room inside. The car has been a great success for Nissan and so many people are already calling for a second generation and some are even pushing Nissan to sell a three door model.

Nissan is currently considering the introduction of several new models including the next generation X-Class crossover that will be based on the upcoming Qashqai. The car has been scheduled to be unveiled in November 2011, but not all models will come out at the same time.
